@startuml 03-timeout-degradation
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Semi-Sync Timeout and Degradation

participant "Client" as client
participant "Master" as master
participant "Slave" as slave
participant "                    " as spacer

== Normal Semi-Sync ==

client -> master : Write Transaction
master -> master : Write to Binlog
master -> slave : Send Binlog
slave --> master : ACK received
master -> master : Commit to InnoDB
master --> client : Return Success

== Slave Dies - Timeout Scenario ==

client -> master : Write Transaction
master -> master : Write to Binlog
master ->x slave : Send Binlog (Failed)

note right of slave #Orange
  Slave unreachable:
  - Network broken
  - Slave crashed
  - Disk failure
end note

master -> master : Waiting for ACK...

note right of master
  rpl_semi_sync_master_timeout
  (default: 10 seconds)
end note

master -> master : Timeout reached (10s)
master -> master : **Degrade to Async Mode**
master -> master : Commit locally
master --> client : Return Success

note over master #Pink
  **Unprotected Period**
  All subsequent transactions
  commit without Slave ACK
end note

== Slave Recovers ==

slave -> master : IO Thread Reconnects
master -> master : Detect Rpl_semi_sync_master_clients = 1
master -> master : Switch Rpl_semi_sync_master_status = ON
slave -> master : Request Binlog (from last position)
master -> slave : Send accumulated backlog

note over master, slave #LightGreen
  **Protection Resumes**
  Next transaction waits for Slave ACK
end note

@enduml
